review:
This game is great! I enjoyed playing it greatly and once every other year, I replay it with different character builds. 

Advantages:
- Engaging, interesting story;
- Interesting magic-technology duality in the in-game world;
- Cool magical abilities; 
- Many funny moments; 
- DIALOGUE: one of the best features of this game. It is really well-written and every message is interesting to read. Some messages are hilarious!
- Many different ways to beat the game: with magic or technology, as a stupid killing machine or an elegant intelligent person, killing everyone you see or playing as a pacifict. 

Disadvantages:
- Bad graphics;
- Unpolished combat system;
- Difficulty disbalance - playing as a technologist is much, MUCH harder than as a magician!

One of the best RPG on PC even if, obviously, technically outdated...
(understand me well, it is not better than the best modern ones but it's very good anyway).

Basically it's fallout (the original) in a steampunk universe.

It's for you if:
- you like fantasy/steampunk genre;
- you like RPG;
- you like large games.

It's not for you if:
- technical aspects are important;
- you can be irritated by a somewhat perfectible gameplay (for instance, travels are very, very slow with respect to the world size);
- you prefer fast games.
